Not a real TV star.
It would be played by a movie star.

114
00:05:47,105 --> 00:05:50,525
- A movie star playing a television star.
- Goldie, Julia, Michelle...

115
00:05:50,734 --> 00:05:52,235
...Bette, Lily.
- Dolly Parton.

116
00:05:52,402 --> 00:05:54,278
- Dolly.
- She would be very good.

117
00:05:54,488 --> 00:05:56,572
- I like Goldie.
- Goldie Goes to Africa.

118
00:05:56,740 --> 00:05:57,949
Great. We have a relationship.

119
00:05:58,116 --> 00:06:01,285
- That would be great. Goldie Goes to Africa.
- Goldie Goes to Africa.

120
00:06:01,453 --> 00:06:03,412
- She becomes worshiped.
- Worshiped?

121
00:06:03,580 --> 00:06:05,581
- Well, she's found by this tribe...
- Yes?

122
00:06:05,749 --> 00:06:07,542
Of small people. But then she has to...

123
00:06:07,709 --> 00:06:10,378
She's found by this tribe
and they worship her. But then...

124
00:06:10,546 --> 00:06:12,672
I see. It's like a Gods Must Be Crazy...

125
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:14,924
...except the Coke bottle's
now a television actress.

126
00:06:15,092 --> 00:06:17,552
Yeah, exactly right.
It's Out of Africa meets Pretty Woman.

127
00:06:17,719 --> 00:06:19,136
And she has to decide...

128
00:06:19,304 --> 00:06:23,182
...whether to stay with the TV show
or save this entire African tribe.

129
00:06:23,392 --> 00:06:24,433
It could be a man.

130
00:06:24,601 --> 00:06:26,853
Hey, where's Griffin Mill's office?
- Right here.

131
00:06:27,020 --> 00:06:30,064
- Hey, you're Martin Scorsese.
- No, but I know Harvey Keitel.

132
00:06:30,232 --> 00:06:33,776
Yeah, I know you do.
Hey, I loved Cape Fear. Ha, ha.

133
00:06:33,944 --> 00:06:36,279
- My old man worked for Hitchcock too.
- Yeah?

134
00:06:36,488 --> 00:06:40,074
Rope. It was a masterpiece.
The story wasn't any good.

135
00:06:40,242 --> 00:06:43,369
He shot the whole thing without cuts.
I hate all this cut, cut, cut.

136
00:06:43,537 --> 00:06:47,039
Oh, yeah, well, what about, uh, Bertolucci,
that great tracking shot...

137
00:06:47,291 --> 00:06:51,002
...with Winger in Sheltering Sky?
- I didn't see it.

138
00:06:52,421 --> 00:06:54,630
Touch of Evil, that was the one.
Welles...

139
00:06:54,798 --> 00:06:56,716
I been here since 8:00. Honest I have.

140
00:06:56,884 --> 00:06:59,802
I stuck my neck out for you to get this job.
Who were you with?

141
00:06:59,970 --> 00:07:04,056
- I was there with, um, Alan Rudolph.
- What were you doing with Alan Rudolph?

142
00:07:04,224 --> 00:07:07,393
Well, no, he asked me to have coffee.
He was telling me this idea.

143
00:07:07,561 --> 00:07:09,270
- What do I say?
- You're my assistant.

144
00:07:09,438 --> 00:07:13,107
- Don't get involved with writers.
- I wasn't. I was just listening to this idea.

145
00:07:13,275 --> 00:07:15,902
- I told him he should give it to you.
- What's your pitch?

146
00:07:16,069 --> 00:07:17,737
Well, does political scare you?

147
00:07:17,946 --> 00:07:20,990
Political doesn't scare me.
Radical political scares me.

148
00:07:21,158 --> 00:07:24,493
- "Political" political scares me.
- This is politely politically radical.

149
00:07:24,661 --> 00:07:25,870
- Is it funny?
- It's funny.

150
00:07:26,079 --> 00:07:28,205
- It's a funny political thing.
- It's a thriller too.

151
00:07:28,415 --> 00:07:30,082
- It's a thriller?
- All at once.

152
00:07:30,334 --> 00:07:31,584
So, uh, what's the story?

153
00:07:31,835 --> 00:07:34,128
Well, I want Bruce Willis.
I think I can talk to him.

154
00:07:34,296 --> 00:07:37,757
Um, it's a story about a senator.
A bad-guy senator at first.

155
00:07:37,966 --> 00:07:40,593
He's traveling around the country
on the country's dime.

156
00:07:40,761 --> 00:07:44,847
- Like that Sununu guy used to do.
- Sort of a cynical, political thriller-comedy?

157
00:07:45,057 --> 00:07:47,266
Yeah, but it's got a heart, uh,
in the right spot.

158
00:07:47,476 --> 00:07:49,936
And anyway, he has an accident.

159
00:07:50,145 --> 00:07:53,230
- An accident?
- Yeah, and he becomes clairvoyant.

160
00:07:53,440 --> 00:07:55,066
- Like a psychic. Yeah.
- Oh, I see.

161
00:07:55,275 --> 00:07:58,402
So it's kind of a psychic, political
thriller-comedy with a heart.

162
00:07:58,612 --> 00:08:02,907
With a heart. And, uh, not unlike Ghost
meets Manchurian Candidate.

163
00:08:03,116 --> 00:08:05,993
- Go on, I'm listening.
- He can start to read people's minds...

164
00:08:06,161 --> 00:08:11,040
...and when he gets to the president's mind,
it's completely blank. Completely blank.

165
00:08:11,208 --> 00:08:13,501
- Can I get you anything?
- I'd like a beer, please.

166
00:08:13,669 --> 00:08:17,380
- We don't have beer.
- Uh, wine. Red wine, please.

167
00:08:18,256 --> 00:08:22,093
Of course, someone gets killed at the end.
They always do in political thrillers.

168
00:08:23,887 --> 00:08:24,887
Griffin Mill's office.

169
00:08:25,055 --> 00:08:26,722
I know. Can you put him on?

170
00:08:26,890 --> 00:08:29,433
- It's an intriguing idea, Jim.
