- Seen my Binaca?

176
00:08:39,736 --> 00:08:41,404
Do you know how many times
I've heard that?

177
00:08:41,571 --> 00:08:44,115
- Who is this?
- If he don't get back to me...

178
00:08:44,282 --> 00:08:45,908
- I read that script.
- Who was that?

179
00:08:46,076 --> 00:08:47,368
I don't know. He didn't say.

180
00:08:47,536 --> 00:08:50,496
- What do you mean, he didn't say?
- How are you gonna cast it?

181
00:08:50,706 --> 00:08:53,666
The lead character is a 50-year-old
female circus performer.

182
00:08:53,834 --> 00:08:56,627
- A fire-eater.
- Let me read the coverage.

183
00:08:56,920 --> 00:08:59,005
Are we still having lunch
with Aaron Camp?

184
00:08:59,172 --> 00:09:01,924
- Yeah, what time?
- I made it for 1:00.

185
00:09:02,259 --> 00:09:04,635
- Bad day?
- He's having writer's block.

186
00:09:06,930 --> 00:09:09,974
You have a meeting with Harders
and Frank South this afternoon.

187
00:09:10,142 --> 00:09:12,268
- What time? I'll be here.
- At 3:00. Okay.

188
00:09:12,436 --> 00:09:13,936
Put the meetings on the computer.

189
00:09:14,104 --> 00:09:15,938
- All right.
- Thanks.

190
00:09:16,106 --> 00:09:18,482
- You going now? I'll go with you.
- I'm going to see Levison.

191
00:09:18,650 --> 00:09:21,152
I'll meet you there.
Order me a salad and Crystal Geyser.

192
00:09:21,361 --> 00:09:22,611
- Okay. Bye.
- Thanks.

